<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Harvest" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Harvest,</orth> 1) the season and act of reaping corn or fruits: <bibl n="shak. tmp 4.115" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. IV, 115</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.4.249" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 4, 249</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 2.7.26" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 7, 26</bibl> <emph>(come to h.).</emph> Metaphorically: <cit><quote>frame the season for your own h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 1.3.27" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado I, 3, 27</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>when wit and youth is come to h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 3.1.143" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 1, 143</bibl></cit> (is ripened). <cit><quote>in's spring became a h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 1.1.46" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 1, 46</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) the corn or fruit reaped: <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.5.103" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 5, 103</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.2.47" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A III, 2, 47</bibl>. Metaphorically, == fruit, produce: Ven. Ded. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.2.47" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A III, 2, 47</bibl> <bibl n="shak. luc 859" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 859</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. son 128.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 128, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.3.326" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 3, 326</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.381" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 1, 381</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.7.21" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C V, 7, 21</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 2.2.115" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 2, 115</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 2.2.115" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 2, 115</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r3 5.2.15" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 15</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 1.4.33" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 4, 33</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 4.2.152" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. IV, 2, 152</bibl>.
